article.headline: IPFW 100, Marygrove College 48
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. (AP) -- Five IPFW players reached double figures in a 100-48 win over Marygrove on Monday night. Quintin Carouthers led with 19 points. Demetrius Johnson had 14, DeWitt Scott scored 12 and Tyler Best and Pat Lepper each had 10 for the Mastodons. IPFW (4-8) led 47-19 at halftime, then scored 53 points in the second half. The Mastodons shot 55 percent from the field and committed just four turnovers while forcing 19. Darryl Gay led Marygrove (6-9) with 14 points and nine rebounds. He was the only Mustang to reach double figures. Marygrove shot 18-for-55 from the field and 4-for-20 from 3-point range. The Mustangs trailed just 17-14 in the opening minutes and 27-19 with 5:49 left in the first half, but IPFW scored the last 20 points of the half to lead by 28 points at the break. IPFW's biggest lead was 54 points with 48 seconds to go.
